Sec. 167.113. CIVIL SUIT AGAINST CORPORATE OFFENDER. If a
corporation or an agent of the corporation acting within the agent's
scope of authority commits an offense under this chapter, the county
attorney of the county in which the violation occurs shall institute
a civil suit on behalf of the state in a court of competent
jurisdiction for collection of the fine.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1451, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

